args: Back in my merc days, ＂see you tomorrow＂\nalways came with a caveat.
One to the tune of ＂if we're still alive.＂
Ahhh, nothin' like a full belly to get a guy\nin the mood for some good, old fashioned\nbloodshed. Hope you fellas can keep up!
Just don't think I'll let you hog the glory.\nThat general's head is mine. Once I cash in\non that bounty, I'll be livin' the cushy life.
Hah hah! That's the spirit, kid.\nYou give 'em hell!
Hey now, don't go rilin' the rookies up.\nCan't spend coin if you're dead.
There's the signal. All right, fellas!\nSee your sorry mugs again soon—\nif we're still alive, that is!
Yeah. See you then. Make sure you\nsurvive so I've got somebody to brag to!
Hey, old timer. Good to see you're\nstill kickin'.
Gah hah hah. Scraped through another\none, so I did!
Glad you're still with us. By the way,\nyou heard anything about that rookie?
Tsk. I knew that stupid kid was in over\nhis head.
Our line a' work's always quick to reward\nthe eager with a swift end.
How many people have I told I'd see them\ntomorrow, only for us to never meet again?\nI lost count early on.
That's about all a merc's life was worth, on\nthe battlefield. Ain't nobody got time to be\nmourning every domino that falls.
You just had to let it go and move on.\nAs a merc, your life is yours to risk or lose.
Hey, guys. Glad you could make it.
(One day I'm leavin' a trail of bodies on\nthe battlefield, and now I'm here playin'\npretend. Ya gotta laugh or you'll cry.)
(Little rays of sunshine, these rascals.\nIt's almost enough to blind a guy.)
Get ready for my super fireball slider!
Heh heh. Okay, your turn to pitch!\nLet's trade spots!
...Okay! I'll give it my best shot!
(I spent my childhood chained to a desk.\nNever got a taste of this carefree stuff.)
(Then, after becoming a merc, well... I got\nmy freedom, but I paid the cost in blood.\nDeath was always around the corner.)
(Tch. I'm startin' to wish I didn't have\nto turn back into a grown-up after all.)
Dang. I thought that pitch was\npretty good, too.
Now, where'd that ball go?\n...Ah! Found it.
What d'you think happened?\nYou reckon he's okay?
No time for thinkin'!\nC'mon, we gotta move. NOW!
